<subSubSection pageId="22" pageNumber="447" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="22.[151,1437,1718,2033]" pageId="22" pageNumber="447">
<emphasis box="[199,288,1755,1781]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="447">Thorax.</emphasis>
Without distinct marking. Wing tinged with dark brown, stigma pale brown. Legs with coxa, trochanters and bases of femora dusky yellow. Halter long, pale yellow.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="22.[151,1437,1718,2033]" pageId="22" pageNumber="447">
<emphasis box="[199,313,1827,1853]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="447">Abdomen.</emphasis>
Sternites dirty yellow; male tergite 8 with long rectangular lobe at middle of posterior margin. Male terminalia with gonocoxite bearing three lobes dorsally; each tip of these lobes with tufts of long setae. Outer gonstylus rod-shaped with small claw-shaped lobe at tip. Paramere with mesal-apical lobe blade-shaped, truncated obliquely at tip, about twice as long as wide. Male body length: 
<quantity box="[870,959,1934,1961]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" pageId="22" pageNumber="447" unit="mm" value="5.5">5.5 mm</quantity>
. Wing length: 6.0 mm.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
